            "text": "but have certain limitations . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In this work , we propose an agent - based model of the epidemic in a confined space of agents representing humans . <S>",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "An extension to the SEIR model allows us to consider the difference between the appearance ( black - box view ) of the spread of disease , and the real situation ( glass - box view ) . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "Our model allows for simulations of lockdowns , social distancing , personal hygiene , quarantine , and hospitalization , with further considerations of different parameters",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "such as the extent",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "to which hygiene and social distancing are observed in a population . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "Our results give qualitative indications of the effects of various policies and parameters ;",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "for instance , that lockdowns by themselves are extremely unlikely to bring an end to an epidemic",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "and may indeed make things worse ,",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
